Summary for data.frame with replicated rows

Source: R/lms.R
summary_c2c.Rd

transforming sumary.lm object according to real number of d.f.

summary_c2c(x, df_old, df_new)

Arguments

x

lm object
df_old

integer number of d.f in orginal dataset
df_new

integer number of d.f in dataset with replicated rows

Value

data.frame

Examples

data(occup)
data(trans)

occup_old <- occup[occup$year == 2008, ]
occup_new <- occup[occup$year == 2010, ]

occup_2 <- cat2cat(
  data = list(old = occup_old, new = occup_new, cat_var = "code", time_var = "year"),
  mappings = list(trans = trans, direction = "backward"),
  ml = list(
    method = "knn",
    features = c("age", "sex", "edu", "exp", "parttime", "salary"),
    args = list(k = 10)
  )
)

# Regression
# we have to adjust size of std as we artificialy enlarge degrees of freedom
lms <- lm(I(log(salary)) ~ age + sex + factor(edu) + parttime + exp, occup_2$old,
  weights = multipier * wei_freq_c2c
)
summary_c2c(lms, df_old = nrow(occup_old), df_new = nrow(occup_2$old))
